field.name: cdcep_answer
field.value: Monetary donations are used to support inpatients, outpatients, homeless Veterans, caregivers of Veterans, and others being treated in VA facilities. Donors can support the general fund, allowing facilities to use donations wherever the greatest need is identified, or identify a specific program such as transportation services, special events, residential care units, or any of the other unique services VA offers.

field.name: cdcep_name
field.value: How does VA use monetary donations?

field.name: cdcep_answer
field.value: When donating online using the Pay.gov platform, the minimum donation is $5.00. If you choose to donate at a facility in person, there is no minimum.

field.name: cdcep_name
field.value: Is there a minimum monetary donation amount?

field.name: cdcep_answer
field.value: Yes, donations to support any of VA's programs are tax deductible, whether you direct that donated funds be used for a specific purpose, or allow VA to decide how they will be used. In addition, 100% of your donation goes to the facility you choose to benefit Veteran's programs and services. The Internal Revenue Service (IRS) has specific guidance for tax deductibility of donations or volunteer time to charitable organizations found in IRS Publication 526: Charitable Contributions.

field.name: cdcep_answer
field.value: You can find medical centers through our website at www.va.gov. E-Donate buttons are available on the individual medical center websites. Clicking on the E-Donate button takes you directly to our secure donation portal.

field.name: cdcep_name
field.value: How can I select a VA Medical Center to make my donation?

field.name: cdcep_answer
field.value: Yes, paying online with Pay.gov is safe, secure, and the preferred method to make a payment.

field.name: cdcep_name
field.value: Will my credit card and bank information be safe if I donate online?

field.name: cdcep_answer
field.value: We ask donors to complete a short form providing their name, address, program for donation (general or specific program) and donation amount. You may also include if you are making a donation in honor or memory of an individual.

field.name: cdcep_name
field.value: What information do I need to provide in order to donate?

field.name: cdcep_answer
field.value: Th VA Financial Service Center Customer Support can help with Pay.gov questions by email at VAFSCCSHD@va.gov or by phone toll-free at (877) 353-9791. Questions about facility donations can be directed to the specific facility found at www.va.gov.
